<refnamediv>
<refname>initexmf</refname>
<refpurpose>&MiKTeX; configuration utility</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>

<cmdsynopsis>
&initexmf;
<arg choice="opt" rep="repeat"><replaceable>option</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>

</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1>

<title>Description</title>

<para>&initexmf; can be used to configure &MiKTeX;.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>User mode vs. administrator mode</title>

<para>This utility can be run in two modes:</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>User mode (default)</term>
<listitem>
<para>&MiKTeX; operates on user-scoped configuration and data files.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>Administrator mode</term>
<listitem>
<para>Only system-wide &MiKTeX; configuration and data files are
modified, assuming that the &MiKTeX; setup is shared by all users.
The utility must be run with administrator privileges.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

<para>By default, the utility runs in user mode.  You can turn on
administrator mode with the <option>--admin</option> option.  For
example, if you want to update the system-wide file name database, you
invoke the utility as follows:</para>

<screen><prompt>&prompt;</prompt><userinput>initexmf --admin --update-fndb</userinput></screen>

</refsect1>

<refsect1>

<title>Options</title>

<variablelist>
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../Options/admin.xml" />
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--default-paper-size=<replaceable>paper</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--default-paper-size=paper</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>paper size</primary>
<secondary>setting default</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Set the default paper size.  <replaceable>paper</replaceable>
must be <option>a4</option> or
<option>letter</option>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../Options/disableinstaller.xml" />
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--dump</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--dump</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>format files</primary>
<secondary>creating</secondary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>memory dump files</primary>
<secondary>creating</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Create all memory dump files.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--dump=<replaceable>name</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Dump the specified memory dump file.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--edit-config-file=<replaceable>configfile</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--edit-config-file=file</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Open the specified config file in a text editor.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../Options/enableinstaller.xml" />
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--engine=<replaceable>engine</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Engine to be used when generating format files.</para></listitem>  
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--force</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--force</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Force <option>--mklinks</option> to overwrite existing
executables.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--list-formats</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--list-formats</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>List all known formats.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--list-modes</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--list-modes</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>METAFONT</primary>
<secondary>modes</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>List all known &METAFONT; modes.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--mklangs</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--mklangs</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Create <filename>language.dat</filename>,
<filename>language.dat.lua</filename> and
<filename>language.def</filename>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--mklinks</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--mklinks</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Create all possible links.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--mklinks=<replaceable>category</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--mklinks=category</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Create links for the specified <replaceable>category</replaceable>, which must be one of:</para>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>formats</option></term>
<listitem><para>Create links from format names to &TeX; engines.  For
example, <filename>latex&EXESUFFIX;</filename> will become a link to
<filename>&MIKTEX_PREFIX;tex&EXESUFFIX;</filename> and invoking
<filename>latex&EXESUFFIX;</filename> will cause &TeX; to load the
format file <filename>latex.fmt</filename>. </para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>miktex</option></term>
<listitem><para>Create links from standard program names to &miktexprefix;
executables.  For example, <filename>tex&EXESUFFIX;</filename> will
become a link to
<filename>&MIKTEX_PREFIX;tex&EXESUFFIX;</filename>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>scripts</option></term>
<listitem><para>Create executable links from script names to script
wrappers.  For example, <filename>latexmk&EXESUFFIX;</filename> will
become a link to the internal &Perl; wrapper
<filename>runperl&EXESUFFIX;</filename> and invoking
<filename>latexmk&EXESUFFIX;</filename> will eventually execute the
&Perl; script <filename>latexmk.pl</filename>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--mkmaps</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--mkmaps</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>psfonts.map</primary>
<secondary>creating</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Build the font map files.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--print-only</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--print-only</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Print what would be done.  Nothing is changed.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--quiet</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--quiet</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Suppress screen output.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--register-root=<replaceable>dir</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--register-root</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>&TEXMF; root</primary>
<secondary>registering</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Register a &TEXMF; root directory.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--remove-links</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--remove-links</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Remove the links which were created by <option>--mklinks</option>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--report</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--report</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Write a &MiKTeX; configuration report.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--set-config-value=[<replaceable>section</replaceable>]<replaceable>valuename</replaceable>=<replaceable>value</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--set-config-value=[section]valuename=value</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Set a value to be stored in the &MiKTeXconfigurationdatastore;
(see <citerefentry><refentrytitle>miktex.ini</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry>).</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--show-config-value=[<replaceable>section</replaceable>]<replaceable>valuename</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--show-config-value=[section]valuename</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Print a value from the &MiKTeXconfigurationdatastore; (see <citerefentry><refentrytitle>miktex.ini</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry>).</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--unregister-root=<replaceable>dir</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--unregister-root</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>&TEXMF; root</primary>
<secondary>unregistering</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Unregister a &TEXMF; root directory.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--update-fndb</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--update-fndb</primary>
</indexterm>
<indexterm>
<primary>file name datasbase</primary>
<secondary>refreshing</secondary>
</indexterm>
<para>Refresh the whole file name database.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--update-fndb=<replaceable>dir</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Refresh the file name database for a specific
&TEXMF; tree.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--user-roots=<replaceable>directories</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Register user root directories.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--verbose</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--verbose</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Print information on what is being done.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--version</option></term>
<listitem>
<indexterm>
<primary>--version</primary>
</indexterm>
<para>Print the version number and exit.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

